nd":"Leicester, Leicestershire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Cooke","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Cook  .","History: Francis Cooke (died 1663) and his eldest son John were passengers on the <i>Mayflower</i> in 1621; they were joined two years later by Francis's wife and other children. In the words of William Bradford, he lived long enough ‘to see his children's children have children’."],"variants":[{"name":"Cook","meanings":["English: occupational name for a cook, a seller of cooked meats, or a keeper of an eating house, from Middle English <i>cok</i>, <i>coke</i>, <i>cook</i>, <i>couk</i>, <i>cuk(e)</i> (Old English <i>cōc</i>) ‘cook’ or ‘seller of cooked foods’. See also   Kew  .","Irish and Scottish: usually identical in origin with the English name (see 1 above), but in some cases a shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Cúg</b> ‘son of Hugo’ (see   McCook  ).","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames meaning ‘cook’, such as German and Jewish   Koch  , Dutch   Kook  , Polish <b>Kucharz</b> and   Kucharczyk  , Slovenian and Croatian   Kuhar  , North German   Kuk  ."]}]},{"name":"Abraham","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, borne by the first of the Jewish patriarchs, with whom God made a covenant that his descendants should possess the land of Canaan. The Hebrew form is <i>Avraham</i>, and is of uncertain derivation. In Genesis 17:5 it is explained as ‘father of a multitude (of nations)’ (Hebrew <i>av hamon (goyim)</i>. It has always been a popular Jewish given name, and was also chosen by Christians, especially by Puritans and other fundamentalists from the 16th century onwards. Various early saints of the Eastern Roman Empire also bore this name. Its currency in the United States was greatly enhanced by the fame of  President Abraham Lincoln  (  1809–65 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Avrom","meanings":["Yiddish form of   Abraham ."]},{"name":"Avraham","meanings":["modern Hebrew form of   Abraham ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Abraham Cooke was born in 1129, in London, England, his father, William Cooke, was 25 and his mother, Elizabeth Winnie Mattha, was 20. He married Margaret Greene in 1154. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1167, in Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1129–1167":"1129–1167","1104–1135":"1104–1135","1106–Male":"1106–Surnud","1131–1170":"1130–1170","1155–1193":"1155–1193","1157–Male":"1157–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1104–1123":"1104–1123","1109–1130":"1109–1130","1154":"1154","1131":"1130","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","1129":"1129","1128":"1128","1106":"1106","1104":"1104","1157":"1157","1135":"1135","1167":"1167","1123":"1123","1155":"1155","1109":"1109","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England","London, England":"London, England","Leicester, Leicestershire, England":"Leicester, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"1129–1167":"1129–1167","1104–1135":"1104–1135","1106–Male":"1106–Kuollut","1131–1170":"1130–1170","1155–1193":"1155–1193","1157–Male":"1157–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1104–1123":"1104–1123","1109–1130":"1109–1130","1154":"1154","1131":"1130","1130":"1130","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1170":"1170","1129":"1129","1128":"1128","1106":"1106","1104":"1104","1157":"1157","1135":"1135","1167":"1167","1123":"1123","1155":"1155","1109":"1109","Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincoln, Lincolnshire, England","London, England":"London, England","Leicester, Leicestershire, England":"Leicester, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"1129–1167":"1129–1167","1104–1135":"1104–1135","1106–Male":"1106–Décédé","1131–1170":"1130–1170","1155–1193":"1155–1193","1157–Male":"1157–Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1104–1123":"1104–1123","1109–1130":